    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN175.1-kilavi1">
          <p type="edition">piriviṉkaṇ vaṟpuṟukkun tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What SHE said to the confidante who consoled [her] during the separation.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN175.1-kilavi2">
          <p type="edition"><app><lem wit="#NL #C1 #C7 #C9 #RK">tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatū[u]mām</lem><rdg wit="#C5 #C9c">talaimakaḷukkut tōḻi colliyatū[u]mām</rdg><rdg wit="#RK">piriviṉkaṇ vēṟupaṭṭa talaimaka ṭōḻikkuc coṟṟatūumām</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">It is also what SHE said to the confidante/what the confidante said to HER/what SHE who had undergone changes during the separation said to the confidante.</p>
        </div>

        <div xml:id="AN175.1">
      <lg type="edition">
        <l>vīṅku<supplied>vi</supplied>ḷim purīiya vicaiyamai nōṉcilai</l>
        <l>vāṅkutoṭai piḻaiyā vaṉka ṇāṭavar</l>
        <l>viṭutoṟum viḷikkum vevvā<supplied>y vāḷi</supplied></l>
        <l><supplied>yāṟu</supplied>cel vampala ruyircelap peyarppiṟ</l>
        <l>pāṟukiḷai payirntu paṭumuṭai kava<supplied>ru</supplied>m</l>
        <l>veñcura miṟanta kātalar neñcuṇa</l>
        <l>variya vañciṉañ <supplied>co</supplied>lliyum paṉmāṇ</l>
        <l>ṭerivaḷai muṉkai paṟṟiyum viṉaimuṭittu</l>
        <l>varutu meṉṟaṉa raṉṟē <supplied>tōḻi</supplied></l>
        <l>koliya ṉeṭuntērk kaivaṇ ceḻiya</l>
        <l>ṉālaṅ kāṉat tamarkaṭan tuyartta</l>
        <l>vēliṉum pallū<supplied>ḻ</supplied> miṉṉi muraceṉa</l>
        <l>māyiru vicumpiṟ kaṭiyiṭi payiṟṟi</l>
        <l>nērkatir niraitta nē<supplied>mi</supplied>ya<supplied>ñ</supplied> celvaṉ</l>
        <l>pōraṭaṅ kakalam poruntiya tārpōṟ</l>
        <l>ṟiruvi ṟēettuk kulaii yurukeḻu</l>
        <l>maṇpayam pūppap pāa<supplied>y</supplied>t</l>
        <l>taṇpeya leḻili tāḻnta pōḻtē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>[Our] lover who has gone to cross the hot desert, (6a-c)</l>
        <l>where, when strong men who do not fail in shooting when bending (2)</l>
        <l>[their] sturdy bows suited for speed that graze the bulging border(?), (1)</l>
        <l>discharge cruel-mouthed arrows that whistle whenever sent off</l>
        <l>so that the lives of strangers going [that] way go, (3f.)</l>
        <l>kites call [their] relatives [and] seize the fallen flesh, (5)</l>
        <l>he spoke difficult oaths while [my] heart absorbed [them], (6d-7c)</l>
        <l>many times gripped [my] forearms with bangles visible (7d-8c)</l>
        <l>and said “we will come [back] after finishing the work” – isn’t it, friend? – (8d-9)</l>
        <l>– at the time when clouds hover with cool rains, (18)</l>
        <l>spreading so that the yield of the earth blooms, (17)</l>
        <l>fearfully shaking the land of the brilliant bow, (16)</l>
        <l>that resembles the garland to be joined to the chest to which they yield in battle (15)</l>
        <l>of the lord with the discus(?) that lines up straight rays, (14)</l>
        <l>repeating speedy thunder in the vast dark sky (13)</l>
        <l>like a drum, flashing many more times than [there were] spears (12)</l>
        <l>that were raised when being victorious in the battle at Ālaṅkāṉam (11)</l>
        <l>by Ceḻiyaṉ generous of hand, with a large chariot of murderous nature. (10)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
